Defendant Michael D Everhart in court, in custody, with attorney Andrew R Rider.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and  Stayed Sentence of:

8 Years Imprisonment CONSECUTIVE TO SOUTH CAROLINA CASE
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 5 Years of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation:  5 years  CONCURRENT TO PROBATION IN SOUTH CAROLINA

Conditions of Probation/Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Obtain a valid license withint the first 6 months;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge;

Cost: $268.00 
DNA surcharge: $250.00
(To be paid during the first 12 months probation.)

Condition Time:  8 months Jail  (First 4 months STRAIGHT TIME.  Remaining  Huber) -  Credit  124 days

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.  Body armor warnings given.
